{"title": "Mark Twain and the Happy Island", "description": "This Mark Twain Memoir by Elizabeth Wallace paints an idyllic portrait of his time in Bermuda, not long before his death in 1910. Wallace and Twain met in Bermuda in 1908, became fast friends, and shared time together on the island and regular correspondence until 6 weeks before Twain's death. According to one academician,  \"Wallace\u2019s deep affection for Twain is evident in her writings, so she also may have wished to burnish his legacy. As a result, Happy Island is a popular treatment in a breezy, occasionally sentimental style. It portrays Twain as a fun and caring friend but only hints at weightier matters.\"   - Summary by John Greenman", "duration": 8639, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "15258", "name": "Elizabeth Wallace"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/mark_twain_happy_island_2009_librivox/mark_twain_happy_island_e_wallace_2009.jpg", "copyright_year": "1913", "genres": ["Biography & Autobiography", "Modern (20th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "CS"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "I. The Sign of the Shell", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mark_twain_happy_island_2009_librivox/marktwainhappyisland_01_wallace_64kb.mp3", "duration": 620}, {"section": 2, "title": "II. How history May Be Taught", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mark_twain_happy_island_2009_librivox/marktwainhappyisland_02_wallace_64kb.mp3", "duration": 527}, {"section": 3, "title": "III. Some Literary Gossip", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mark_twain_happy_island_2009_librivox/marktwainhappyisland_03_wallace_64kb.mp3", "duration": 577}, {"section": 4, "title": "IV. Spanish Point", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mar